<p>I have a view that outputs Name, Field, Value like so:  </p>  <pre><code> Name | Field | Value   ------|-------|------ Item1 |  SKU  | 83841   Item1 |  UOM  | EA   Item1 |  QTY  | 47   Item2 |  SKU  | 83458   Item2 |  UOM  | PK   Item2 |  QTY  | 88 </code></pre>  <p>And I want to get:  </p>  <pre><code> Name |  SKU  | UOM | QTY   ------|-------|-----|---- Item1 | 83841 | EA  | 47 Item2 | 83458 | PK  | 88 </code></pre>  <p>I have tried Pivot, but if I aggregate Name, then I only get one value.  Here is my query:  </p>  <pre><code>SELECT SKU, UOM, QTY FROM (     SELECT Field, Value     FROM dbo.ProductExport ) d PIVOT (     MAX(FieldValue)     for Value in (SKU, UOM, QTY) ) piv; </code></pre>  <p>I feel like it just might not be possible without a unique value, but I might just be missing something too.</p>